# Basic predicate logic
∀x. P(x) → Q(x)
¬P(a)
P(a) ∧ Q(a)
∃y. R(y) ∧ ¬S(y)

# Chained implications and quantifiers
∀x. (P(x) ∧ Q(x)) → R(x)
∀x. ∃y. Loves(x, y) → Happy(x)
∃z. (Smart(z) ∧ Hardworking(z)) → Successful(z)

# Nested negation and conjunctions
¬(P(b) ∨ Q(b))
¬(P(b) ∧ Q(b))
¬∀x. P(x)
¬∃x. Q(x)

# Equivalence and biconditional
∀x. P(x) ↔ Q(x)
P(c) ↔ ¬Q(c)

# Functions and relations
∀x. ∀y. Parent(x, y) → Ancestor(x, y)
∀x. ∀y. Ancestor(x, y) → (∃z. Parent(x, z) ∧ Ancestor(z, y))

# Equality and substitution
a = b
∀x. x = x
∀x. ∃y. x = y → P(y)

# More complex nesting
∃x. (∀y. Follows(y, x) ∧ ∃z. Leads(x, z)) → Influencer(x)
∀x. (¬P(x) ∨ (Q(x) ∧ R(x))) → S(x)

# Mixed symbolic logic
∀x ∈ Humans. Mortal(x)
¬Mortal(Socrates)
Human(Socrates)
Human(Aristotle) ∧ Philosopher(Aristotle)

# Identity reasoning
∀x. Philosopher(x) → Thinker(x)
∃x. Thinker(x) ∧ ¬Philosopher(x)

# Contradictions to test
P(d)
¬P(d)
Q(e)
¬Q(e) ∧ Q(e)
